abstract: >-
  A concept memory framework where every ConceptNode in a symbolic
  graph owns a multi-facet parameter bundle, consumed on demand by
  task-specific muscle modules via a contextual-collapse operation.
  Empirically, the same framework induces bundle geometry that
  tracks each task's topology — linear for numbers, circular for
  colors, 2-D lattice for a spatial grid, prototype-clustered for
  categorical phonemes — with no domain-specific architectural
  change. Cross-muscle alignment is governed by facet-level
  algebraic compatibility (hypothesis H5″, populated across all
  four cells of a 2 × 2 schema). A post-hoc bundle swap establishes
  causal ownership via textbook double dissociation.
keywords:
